The Russia successfully, in just five years, bring his vision of a direct alliance between the Russia and the rich Western countries, strongly consumer of gas, and the fields are in decline.
"This pipeline is a component of our partnership with the Russia, it is a new artery which links us organic way," confirmed François Fillon in inaugurating this pipeline, showing how the major gas contracts are also political and economic.
All of this explains the broad smiles displayed by the leaders of Gazprom, present in numbers in Lubmin, point of arrival of the gas.
The construction of this pipeline is also a technical feat.
The underwater tube is wrapped steel concrete to protect against the anchors of ships.
It rests on the bottom of the sea, 200 m on average.
To build, it took avoid minefields dating from the second world war.
"A hundred had to be removed or destroyed, as a precaution," said Jens Müller, spokesperson of the company Nord Stream.
It also took more measures to protect the fauna and flora.
The tube is a long metal, heavy as 242 Eiffel Towers, that nothing stops along its length: valve, or maintenance station.
A control platform was planned off the coast of the Sweden, but the project is abandoned while the Swedes were unwilling to see a Russian State company to establish a permanent off their coasts.
"Damage, we stop the passage of gas in under a minute," said Jens Müller.
Leaks, gas in the pipeline therefore escapes into the air.
But this case is considered unlikely by builders who expected welds for a leak every 100,000 years.
The State of the pipeline are monitored by a robot submarine, dragged by a ship, for external observation, and a device that circulates within the pipeline.
The shape of a cigar, it is introduced inside the tube, large of one metre in diameter, and it is being pushed by the gas.
Upon arrival, after three full days of travel at the speed of 3 metres second, it delivers accurate information about potential deformations of the metal.
The pipeline was designed to function 50 years without any remedy.
The flow of gas is simply under pressure.
It is 200 bars in the first place, and 100 on arrival.
Five companies have joined forces to implement this project.
The leader is Gazprom, retains 51% of the shares.
Is are joined the German E.ON and BASF (15.5% each), and the Dutch Gasunie and the French GDF Suez Group (9% each).
These five companies have created a joint venture, called Nord Stream, build and operate the pipeline.
It has its headquarters in Zug, in Switzerland, where taxation is particularly favourable.
Gazprom then leased to the company for twenty years renewable, all of the transport capacity of gas.
"Gazprom pay for total capacity, regardless of the amount of gas actually transported", says Jens Müller.
The financing of the construction of the pipeline has provided 30% by shareholders and 70% by bank loans.
The total cost of the project is expected to reach EUR 7.4 billion for the two tubes.
For GDF Suez, for example, investment is up to 240 million.
But minority shareholders are sure to recoup their investment, since only Gazprom assumes the risk.
